cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
1) cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper is about robotic grasp planning and involves a dataset of successful grasps on physical robots. 
2) cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as deep learning is often used in grasp planning and computer vision techniques may be used to analyze the grasp demonstrations. 
3) cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper mentions the use of deep learning in grasp planning. 
4) cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper involves the development of a new method for collecting naturalistic grasp examples. 
5) cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a possible category as the paper discusses a new human grasp demonstration method.
